values:
I genuinely believe that, thus far, this year can be classified as one with a lot of struggle and not a lot of luck.&nbsp; To the outside naked eye a new job and a new car should be elements befitting a great year, but alas, those things are overshadowed.&nbsp;&nbsp;
To keep everyone up on the highlights: yes, I got a new car, as was mentioned in my previous update.&nbsp; Last Tuesday I was T-boned however and for the last four days my car has been in the shop having two new doors put on the driver's side.&nbsp; To be quite honest, had I been in the Neon still, I probably would have been injured... thank you Saturn Ion plastic outter shell with super rebound action. Irony that my first car payment for said car came due the same week it requires a $550 deductible paid on it's repairs. Hopefully, the person who collided with me's insurance will pick it up since I was not at fault.&nbsp;
In the continuing saga of my mother's health reflecting that of the vehicle I am driving: my mom went back into the hospital and they are unsure what is wrong with&nbsp; her exactly (hence her being there for day three even as I write this).&nbsp; Add to that the fact that my parents car has been in the shop the last few days and you have bliss within our household all around.
With the exception of those things; the job front is mixed.&nbsp; I have met a lot of great people and a lot of not so great people.&nbsp; Fortunately the former outweigh the latter in quantity and&nbsp;amount of interaction necessary&nbsp;most of the time.&nbsp; I've even started spending time outside of work with quite a few of them.&nbsp; I'm not making a lot, but I am starting to look over my budget for moving out in the next few months. I've had two people offer to sell me their condos, but I don't know that a condo is really an affordable consideration for me at this point, maybe in a few years.&nbsp; I still haven't completely ruled out just packing up and moving out of state, but since I don't have the overwhelming urge to relocate to any particular place it would be silly to start packing my bags.&nbsp;
In any case, I hope all is well for anyone who managed to read all the way to the bottom; take care!

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I can't remember clearly what I posted last or when.&nbsp; I believe it was a long time ago that I actually typed out anything of substance on here.&nbsp; Needless to say life has been somewhat insane.&nbsp; My car has progressed to full-on seizures that scared even one of the car guys at work when he drove it to check it out. The last time it made a voyage to Utica I ended up having to call Scott and Justin to come pour in oil and shake their heads at me for having the car this long (thank God your husband is a sweetie Jen, lol.)&nbsp; In any case, I know you are asking: well, why haven't you bought a new car yet? Yes, I know.&nbsp; I haven't really had a lot of time to look since I was hired in as an Account Coordinator in March.&nbsp; I've been working a lot of 9-12 hour days. 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yesterday was the first day I've had off in a while, but that was only because my mom went in for another surgery.&nbsp; It is a follow up to the first and they have her heavily sedated with drugs to keep the pain at bay. So say a little prayer for her tonight if that is your thing.&nbsp; She will have an epidural in until at least Friday and I don't know when she will be getting out.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hmm, what else is new?... My friend Josh is in the Avon Players and they are putting on "Do Black Patent Leather Shoes Really Reflect Up?" but when I called the box office for tickets last weekend they were sold out... and now I hear this weekend is sold out too, so they must be doing something good.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
In any case, i need to head out and get to the hospital to visit, so take care all!
